comments: Green (GSW) makes marginal contact with Leonard's (POR) front during the dunk attempt.

MOB shows Turner (POR) absorbs the initiated contact from Green (GSW) after his gather, some of which occurs to his head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled. LAR shows Turner (POR) makes clean contact with the ball thereafter and a jump ball is correctly assessed.
Hood (POR) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Leonard (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Thompson's (GSW) path after the hand-off and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Thompson (GSW) briefly has his arm around Leonard's (POR) upper half before correcting.
Looney (GSW) does not intentionally kick the ball when it makes contact with his foot.
Turner (POR) and Looney (GSW) make incidental contact with one another as they each attempt to gain control of the loose ball.
Thompson (GSW) makes marginal contact with McCollum's (POR) arm during the drive to the basket.
Livingston (GSW) firms up in his screening position in Hood's (POR) path and absorbs the contact.
Lillard (POR) and Livingston (GSW) engage and disengage without affecting the other's FOM.
Thompson (GSW) makes marginal contact with Lillard (POR) that does not affect his ability to control the hand-off.
Thompson (GSW) makes some body contact with Lillard (POR) after the release of his jump shot attempt, but it is marginal and does not affect his ability to land safely.
Looney (GSW) firms up in his screening position in Hood's (POR) path and gives him room to avoid the contact, which Looney absorbs.
LLS shows Leonard (POR) swings down and makes contact across Curry's (GSW) arm/shoulder, causing him to lose control of the ball after his gather.
Curry (GSW) takes more than two steps after his gather.
Livingston (GSW) briefly has his hand on McCollum's (POR) opposite side hip before correcting.
Thompson (GSW) makes marginal contact with Lillard's (POR) off-arm that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Collins (POR) makes marginal contact with Green (GSW) during the inbound.
Thompson (GSW) wraps Lillard's (POR) midsection and affects his FOM.
McKinnie (GSW) makes marginal contact with McCollum's (POR) front at the end of the drive and does not affect his ability to gather.
Leonard (POR) firms up in his screening position in McKinnie's (GSW) path and delivers some contact, but does not affect McKinnie's ability to defend.
There is no clear and conclusive video evidence determining if McKinnie (GSW) makes any contact with McCollum (POR) as he is airborne during the jump shot attempt.
Lillard (POR) and McKinnie (GSW) engage and disengage during rebounding.
Turner (POR) makes incidental contact with McKinnie's (GSW) arm after the release of his shot attempt near the rim that does not affect his ability to follow through naturally.
Curry (GSW) briefly has his arm around McCollum's (POR) midsection before correcting.
Looney (GSW) makes marginal body contact with McCollum (POR) that does not affect his SQBR along the perimeter.
Thompson (GSW) makes marginal contact with Turner's (POR) front prior to making clean contact with the ball.
Thompson (GSW) makes marginal contact with Turner's (POR) backside after his gather.
Green (GSW) makes incidental contact with Turner (POR) that does not affect his ability to get to the rebound.
Looney (GSW) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two legal steps thereafter.
Hood (POR) briefly has his arms around Curry's (GSW) midsection before correcting.
McCollum (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Thompson's (GSW) path and delivers some contact, but it is marginal and does not affect Thompson's ability to defend.
Green (GSW) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly deflects the pass intended for Leonard (POR).
[Observable in enhanced video] Leonard (POR) is in the lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.

Curry's (GSW) drive to the basket originates outside the LDB and the secondary defender Hood (POR) does not fully clear the RA as contact is made with Curry following the release of his driving shot attempt.

LAR shows Thompson (GSW) absorbs the body contact made with Lillard (POR) during the driving shot attempt.  LLB shows Green (GSW) cleanly makes contact with the ball and is the last player to touch the ball before it goes OOB.
Thompson (GSW) and Lillard (POR) engage and disengage without affecting the other's FOM.
Green (GSW) engages and disengages with Leonard (POR) without affecting his FOM during the inbound.
Thompson (GSW) legally contests Lillard's (POR) jump shot attempt.
